Uses of Package
fr.sorbonne_u.cps.dht_mapreduce.interfaces.mapreduce

  • Packages that use fr.sorbonne_u.cps.dht_mapreduce.interfaces.mapreduce 
    Package Description
    fr.sorbonne_u.cps.dht_mapreduce.interfaces.endpoints
    Java interfaces used to describe end points of content nodes of the DHT in the DHT/MapReduce project.
    fr.sorbonne_u.cps.dht_mapreduce.interfaces.frontend
    Interfaces used in the front end of the DHT.
    fr.sorbonne_u.cps.dht_mapreduce.interfaces.mapreduce
    Interfaces used in the nodes of the DHT to provide the map/reduce capabilities.
    fr.sorbonne_u.cps.mapreduce.endpoints  
  • Classes in fr.sorbonne_u.cps.dht_mapreduce.interfaces.mapreduce used by fr.sorbonne_u.cps.dht_mapreduce.interfaces.endpoints 
    Class and Description
    MapReduceSyncI
    The interface MapReduceSyncI defines the methods implementing the map and the reduce computations over the DHT.
  • Classes in fr.sorbonne_u.cps.dht_mapreduce.interfaces.mapreduce used by fr.sorbonne_u.cps.dht_mapreduce.interfaces.frontend 
    Class and Description
    CombinatorI
    The functional interface CombinatorI allows to define functions in the reduce part of the map/reduce protocol that combines two accumulators of type A into one accumulator also of type A.
    ProcessorI
    The functional interface ProcessorI allows to define functions in the map part of the map/reduce protocol that process individual data of type ContentDataI to produce individual results of type R.
    ReductorI
    The functional interface ReductorI allows to define functions in the reduce part of the map/reduce protocol that reduce a result of type R from the map part with an accumulator of type A to produce a new accumulator of type A.
    SelectorI
    The functional interface SelectorI allows to define functions in the map part of the map/reduce protocol that select individual data of type ContentDataI that will be processed.
